p: A sign on the door reads: "\bAbandoned Wing: KEEP OUT!\c[0]".
\rAn abandoned wing?\nNice find, \pn! This might just be where the prophecy is stored!
\bI agree. Nobody knows the prophecy except for the leaders of the cults.\nIt would have to be hidden somewhere most people wouldn't look.
\bAre you three going into the Abandoned Wing?\nMay I ask what about it interests you?
\rOh... we were going to look for a very old book, sir.
\rWe're trainers, you see.\nWe want to protect the region, and we figured that that one prophecy about the cults might be back here.
\bI see. You'd be surprised at how many people've looked for that prophecy.
\bI'll let you in, if you want.
\bThere's no prophecy back there, but there's that one glowing orb.
\bThat's right. It's been there since this library was built.
\bIt's only one of many different odds and ends lying around in the wing.
\bFor whatever reason, people believe it has something to do with the prophecy, so they'll try to get it to react to them.
\bI've already seen hundreds of people leave disappointed.\nDo you really want to waste your time?
\bWell, we may as well try, right?
\rDamian, for once in your life, you're right.
\rLet us in, please. I promise we'll be quick.
\bFine, but we really will need to be fast. I have a lot of things do today.
\bThe glowing orb is in the far end of the Abandoned Wing.\nI'll take you to go see it.
\bBe careful though, there are both wild Pokemon and possibly even trainers back here.
\rLet's go find out what the future holds.

\bDid you know that Smeargle can learn the most moves of any Pokemon?
\bThat's because it's the only one that learns "Sketch"!
